Applies strict Windows SCHANNEL hardening by disabling legacy SSL/TLS protocols and weak ciphers, then enforcing an AEAD-only cipher suite policy using AES-GCM cipher suites.

Detailed Description

This PowerShell script implements a high-security SCHANNEL configuration by:

Verifying Administrator privileges before making changes.
Disabling insecure and deprecated protocols:
SSL 2.0
SSL 3.0
TLS 1.0
TLS 1.1
Enabling only TLS 1.2.
Configuring both Client and Server SCHANNEL settings.
Disabling legacy and vulnerable ciphers:
Triple DES (3DES)
RC4 (128-bit and 56-bit variants)
DES
NULL ciphers
Enforcing a restricted cipher suite policy through Group Policy registry settings.
Limiting TLS negotiations to authenticated encryption (AEAD) cipher suites:
TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256
TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384
Blocking fallback to weaker CBC-based and non-forward-secret cipher suites.
Providing configuration status output and verification messages.
Security Benefits
Eliminates obsolete SSL and early TLS versions.
Removes ciphers vulnerable to attacks such as:
SWEET32 (3DES)
RC4 cryptographic weaknesses
DES brute-force attacks
Enforces Forward Secrecy through ECDHE key exchange.
Restricts encryption to AES-GCM authenticated encryption modes.
Reduces attack surface by allowing only modern cipher suites.




[CmdletBinding()]
param ()

begin {

    function Test-IsElevated {
        $id = [System.Security.Principal.WindowsIdentity]::GetCurrent()
        $p = New-Object System.Security.Principal.WindowsPrincipal($id)
        $p.IsInRole([System.Security.Principal.WindowsBuiltInRole]::Administrator)
    }

    if (-not (Test-IsElevated)) {
        Write-Error "Access Denied. Run as Administrator."
        exit 1
    }

    $protocolBase = "HKLM:\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\SecurityProviders\SCHANNEL\Protocols"
    $cipherBase   = "HKLM:\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\SecurityProviders\SCHANNEL\Ciphers"
    $configBase   = "HKLM:\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Cryptography\Configuration\SSL\00010002"
}

process {

    # ---------------------------
    # TLS PROTOCOL HARDENING
    # ---------------------------
    $protocols = @(
        @{ Name="SSL 2.0"; Enabled=0; Default=1 },
        @{ Name="SSL 3.0"; Enabled=0; Default=1 },
        @{ Name="TLS 1.0"; Enabled=0; Default=1 },
        @{ Name="TLS 1.1"; Enabled=0; Default=1 },
        @{ Name="TLS 1.2"; Enabled=1; Default=0 }
    )

    foreach ($p in $protocols) {

        foreach ($role in @("Server","Client")) {

            $path = "$protocolBase\$($p.Name)\$role"

            New-Item $path -Force | Out-Null
            New-ItemProperty -Path $path -Name "Enabled" -Value $p.Enabled -PropertyType DWord -Force | Out-Null
            New-ItemProperty -Path $path -Name "DisabledByDefault" -Value $p.Default -PropertyType DWord -Force | Out-Null
        }

        Write-Output "$($p.Name) configured."
    }

    # ---------------------------
    # LEGACY CIPHER DISABLE (NON-AEAD)
    # ---------------------------

    $legacyCiphers = @(
        "Triple DES 168",
        "RC4 128/128",
        "RC4 56/128",
        "DES 56/56",
        "NULL"
    )

    foreach ($cipher in $legacyCiphers) {

        $path = "$cipherBase\$cipher"

        New-Item $path -Force | Out-Null
        New-ItemProperty -Path $path -Name "Enabled" -Value 0 -PropertyType DWord -Force | Out-Null

        Write-Output "Disabled legacy cipher: $cipher"
    }

    # ---------------------------
    # FORCE AEAD-ONLY CIPHER SUITES
    # ---------------------------
    $aeadSuites = @(
        "TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_128_GCM_SHA256",
        "TLS_ECDHE_RSA_WITH_AES_256_GCM_SHA384"
    )

    $suiteString = ($aeadSuites -join ",")

    New-Item $configBase -Force | Out-Null
    New-ItemProperty -Path $configBase -Name "Functions" -Value $suiteString -PropertyType String -Force | Out-Null

    Write-Output "AEAD cipher suite policy applied:"
    foreach ($s in $aeadSuites) {
        Write-Output "  - $s"
    }

    # ---------------------------
    # 3DES explicit mapping note
    # ---------------------------
    Write-Output ""
    Write-Output "3DES STATUS: DISABLED (affects TLS_RSA_WITH_3DES_EDE_CBC_SHA and variants)"

    # ---------------------------
    # FINAL OUTPUT
    # ---------------------------
    Write-Output ""
    Write-Output "TLS HARDENING COMPLETE (AEAD-ONLY MODE)"
}

end {}
